Build a router where route paths and parameters are fully typed.
API:

typescript
const router = createRouter({
  '/users/:userId': (params: { userId: string }) => {},
  '/posts/:postId/comments/:commentId': (params: { postId: string; commentId: string }) => {},
});

router.navigate('/users/123'); // OK
router.navigate('/users/123/extra'); // Type error
Requirements:

Use template literal types to parse route patterns.

Extract parameter names into typed objects.

Type-safe navigate() and link() functions.

Support query parameters with optional typing.
Modules:

router/parser.ts (path parsing utilities).

router/index.ts (main router class).

router/types.ts (utility types).
Tests:

Route matching with different patterns.

Type errors for invalid paths.

Parameter extraction correctness.

